dct_title_s: Vera delineatio maris insularum portuum et littorum
dct_description_sm: a Iohanne Hugonis Linschotio; Ioann. a Doetechum, Baptista a Doet. fecerunt.
Bar scale on map given in "Vyftyn Duytsche mylen."
Oriented with north toward bottom of sheet.
Title cartouche to far left; dedication cartouche to far right.
Decorative cartouches, coats of arms, compass roses, rhumb lines, ships, whales.
"Souffrir pour parvenir, A H Linschoten scrib. Anno 1594."
Dutch translation in right half of title cartouche.

Appears in Linschoten's Voyagie, ofte schip-vaert, van Ian Huyghen van Linschoten, van by Noorden om langes Noorvvegan de Noortcaep, Laplant, Vinlant, Ruslandt, de Witte Zee, de custen van Candenoes, Svvetennoes, Pitzora, 1601.
